    <item>
      <title>Yo, Forest! - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/22/yo-forest/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/22/yo-forest/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2025 04:08:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13275" class="post-13275 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Yo, Forest!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;As expected, I found Ruby&amp;#8217;s goodbye letter in the mail today. I wonder if she&amp;#8217;s up there, looking down at us. From the moon, most likely. 🌚&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8163-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Like, to Jeff, I'm gonna move. It's hard to leave, since we're BFFs and stuff... But I have a picture of you that I took when you weren't looking, so I'll never forget you! Like, from Ruby!" class="wp-image-13276" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I also got a letter from the snowman I built last week. He sent me a snowman fridge, which I sold for a cool 8,888 bells. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Antonio was sick with a cold, so I went to the store to buy him some medicine. Get well soon, Ant-Man! 🐜&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At the Roost tonight, I asked K.K. Slider for a random song and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Blues&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8164-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Blues." class="wp-image-13277" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Marina, she tried to describe hip-hop music&amp;#8230;or at least, according to Antonio.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8165-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Marina: According to Antonio, it's all... YO! Yo, Forest... YO! Marina in the house!" class="wp-image-13278" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;To get a better idea of the music, maybe she should have a chat with another octopus-like character named Marina&amp;#8230;from Splatoon 2. 🐙🎶&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Robin asked me to find her a centipede, and I agreed to help out. However, it took me a while to track one down. But I did find one eventually, after 20+ minutes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8166-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Robin: Is this...? It IS! You brought the centipede I wanted!" class="wp-image-13279" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After all that searching, Robin rewarded me with just a CD player. Forget the CD, &lt;em&gt;I&amp;#8217;m&lt;/em&gt; the one that was spinning around town, circling around from rock to rock, looking for the centipede. And she brought the music to a screeching halt with that gift. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The snow will be gone in just a few more days! Bring on spring! I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/22/yo-forest/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-22T23:08:42-05:00"&gt;February 22, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-22T23:11:05-05:00"&gt;February 22, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8163-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Curt Shilling...for Lyle - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/22/curt-shilling-for-lyle/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/22/curt-shilling-for-lyle/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2025 01:56:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7969" class="post-7969 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Curt Shilling&amp;#8230;for Lyle&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I received an odd letter from Mom in the mail. She told me to &amp;#8220;eat them, raise them, or sell them.&amp;#8221; She then &amp;#8220;clarified&amp;#8221; (but not really) by saying that she&amp;#8217;s not talking about my animal friends! So what &lt;em&gt;was &lt;/em&gt;she talking about? 🤔&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/mom-eat-them-150x112.jpg" alt="Dear Jeff, Eat them, raise them, or sell them. No, I'm not talking about your little animal friends! I'd eat it. -Love, Mom" class="wp-image-7970" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I like the bubble wrap paper!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I got the answer when I saw the attached item: a peach. Okay, that makes more sense. 😛 The peach is a foreign fruit, but it&amp;#8217;s not one that I needed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Filbert asked me to deliver a letter to Tank, and Tank was nice enough to show me the letter. It was just as weird as you&amp;#8217;d expect from Filbert: &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/filbert-ate-letter-150x112.jpg" alt="To my bud, Tank, I was so hungry that I ate your letter! You'll come see me again tomorrow, right? Yay! See you! -Filbert" class="wp-image-7971" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Wow, he literally ate his words. That&amp;#8217;s one way to stamp out hunger.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I returned to Filbert, he thanked me for delivering the letter. He also gave me a fairy-tale wall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, there was a new &amp;#8220;Talking to Myself&amp;#8221; message posted to the bulletin board. It was about having picnics by yourself. 🧺&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ttm-picnic-150x112.jpg" alt="-Talking to Myself- As a kid, I always wanted to have picnics by myself. But then I got lonely, so I stopped. Too bad..." class="wp-image-7972" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Curt started telling me a story about how he slipped on the ice and got snow up his nose! 😆 I like this story already!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/curt-nose-150x112.jpg" alt="Curt: After I slipped on the ice and got all this snow up my nose..." class="wp-image-7974" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But his amusing story took a sudden turn. It turns out that he was just shilling for Lyle (who was in town today) and his insurance company!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/curt-insurance-150x112.jpg" alt="Curt: ...I thought that I should have gotten insurance... Hindsight IS always 20/20." class="wp-image-7975" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He had snow up his nose, but insurance on his mind.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t help out Lyle, man! They &lt;em&gt;otter &lt;/em&gt;be ashamed of themselves.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tank was talking about the brain freeze you get from a really cold drink, and he said it makes him feel like he&amp;#8217;s getting &amp;#8220;smarter and &lt;em&gt;smarterer&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/tank-smarter-150x112.jpg" alt="Tank: I just FEEL myself getting smarter and smarterer... kerPOW!" class="wp-image-7976" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Somehow, I don&amp;#8217;t think that&amp;#8217;s what&amp;#8217;s happening. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If you haven&amp;#8217;t seen my latest Wild World video, which I posted last weekend, here it is. It&amp;#8217;s episode 74:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: Wild World #74" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/i8EmQbBcb3g?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you next time!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/22/curt-shilling-for-lyle/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-22T20:56:30-05:00"&gt;February 22, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-22T20:59:06-05:00"&gt;February 22, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/mom-eat-them.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Room Sketch App - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/21/room-sketch-app/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/21/room-sketch-app/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 22 Feb 2025 04:41:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8620" class="post-8620 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Room Sketch App&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, I received my letter from Katrina with my newly purchased lucky item. Unfortunately, it was another &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/"&gt;gold turtle figurine&lt;/a&gt;, and not one of the &lt;em&gt;other &lt;/em&gt;lucky items. I&amp;#8217;ll have to hope for more bad luck in the future to get the other items. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I went out to Lottie&amp;#8217;s island on Monday, Niko told me that Lottie wanted to see me for something. I had no idea what this was about, so I went into the office. She told me to pull out my phone, because she had a new app to send me!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lottie-app-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Lottie: Can you pull out your phone so I can send an app to you?" class="wp-image-8621" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s an app called &amp;#8220;Room Sketch,&amp;#8221; and it&amp;#8217;s used to create room layouts. You can experiment with design ideas, and use them when you create a vacation home for a client.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/room-sketch-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Room sketches created in this app can also be used later when decorating a client's vacation home, making it a great tool for testing your designs!" class="wp-image-8622" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Of course, designing rooms isn&amp;#8217;t exactly my favorite thing. So I just made this masterpiece of a room and then saved and quit the app. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sketch-froggy-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="A mostly empty room with just two froggy chairs in it." class="wp-image-8623" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, I listened in on a conversation between Bob and June. Bob asked June for a book recommendation&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bob-june-book-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Bob: Heeeey, June? Can you suggest me a book?" class="wp-image-8624" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;June&amp;#8217;s reply was just savage. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/june-bob-read-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="June: Oh! You read, Bob? That's rather surprising." class="wp-image-8625" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She recommended &lt;em&gt;Be the &amp;#8220;Y&amp;#8221; in DIY&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Gyroids 2.0&lt;/em&gt;. But then Bob asked which book had more pictures. June said neither, so Bob said he wanted to watch the movie versions instead of reading. I guess June was right about him after all. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bob-movie-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Bob: OK... Which one got turned into the bester movie? I can snack while I watch!" class="wp-image-8626" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Ketchup, I saw that my other short peppy villager (Agent S, of course) was there too. Ketchup even acknowledged that Agent S was visiting&amp;#8230; So when Ketchup said &lt;em&gt;this&lt;/em&gt;, I was a bit confused&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ketchup-anchovy-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Ketchup: That's why I like hanging out with my anchovy here..." class="wp-image-8627" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I legitimately thought Ketchup was calling Agent S her &amp;#8220;anchovy&amp;#8221; as a pet name! But it turns out that she was talking about her actual anchovy, the fish. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I went diving and caught a scallop. Pascal popped up and started talking about ice cream. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pascal-ice-cream2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: You gotta be careful what you wish for in life. Unless you wish for ice cream. That's pretty safe." class="wp-image-8628" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This is not his only quote about ice cream, either. He also had &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/08/28/final-fireworks-24/"&gt;this one&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#8230;as well as an &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2021/04/10/spring-fish-tourney-2021/"&gt;octopus one&lt;/a&gt; that mentions ice cream cones. I think the dude likes ice cream. 🍦&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gulliver was in town, so I helped him out. The next day, he sent me another candy-skull mask.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tonight, I found another scallop and got some more words of wisdom from Pascal. This time, he was talking about the expression &amp;#8220;hold your horses.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pascal-horses-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: When someone tells you to hold your horses, you tell them no. Maaan, they're way too heavy!" class="wp-image-8629" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Whoa&lt;/em&gt;, you&amp;#8217;re right.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Flick was buzzing around town tonight, so I sold him 14 bugs (mostly dung beetles and Rajah Brooke&amp;#8217;s birdwings) for a total of 56,700 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy your weekend, and I&amp;#8217;ll be back with more next week!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/21/room-sketch-app/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-21T23:41:09-05:00"&gt;February 21, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-21T23:43:20-05:00"&gt;February 21, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lottie-app-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sweet Mama Bear - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/02/19/sweet-mama-bear/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/02/19/sweet-mama-bear/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 20 Feb 2025 01:54:39 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18126" class="post-18126 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sweet Mama Bear&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On February 6th, I found a lost item (a bag) on the ground. I returned it to Boots, and he said it was a bag of sand!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250206_HNI_0071-250x150.jpg" alt="Boots: But...it seems a little lighter than it was before. I had a bunch of sand in it for weight training." class="wp-image-18127" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He said it felt lighter than it was before, so he wonders if someone grabbed a handful of sand and ran off! Why would anyone do that? We have a whole beach full of sand in walking distance from anywhere in town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250206_HNI_0072-250x150.jpg" alt="Boots: Do you think someone could have grabbed a handful and run off?" class="wp-image-18128" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But he still thanked me for returning the bag, and he rewarded me with a lotus tee.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the mail, I found a letter from Nintendo with a Flower Fairy dress attached. It was a reward for playing Animal Crossing Puzzle League last month. I must&amp;#8217;ve met some goal or other criteria without realizing it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Last Friday (February 14th), Jeremiah told me that he was going to leave town on the 16th! I made him change his mind, but that was another close call!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250214_HNI_0004-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: I'm leaving on the 16th of this month!" class="wp-image-18129" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Not this time, you&amp;#8217;re not.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Since it was Valentine&amp;#8217;s Day, I went to the Roost to get a special cup of hot chocolate from Brewster. Such a sweet treat!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250214_HNI_0010-250x150.jpg" alt="This must be...hot chocolate!" class="wp-image-18130" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I also had some Valentine&amp;#8217;s Day letters in the mail. Isabelle sent me a chocolate cake, Lolly sent me a chocolate heart, and Mom sent me a comfy sweater. Of those three, the sweater tasted the worst.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday (Tuesday), I found a lost glove on the ground near my eastern ramp. I later returned it to its owner, Rolf. It&amp;#8217;s such a big glove that I should&amp;#8217;ve known it was his! 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250218_HNI_0021-250x150.jpg" alt="...I wonder if someone dropped this. Maybe I should look for the owner and return it?" class="wp-image-18134" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He thanked me for returning it, and he rewarded me with his Mama bear.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250218_HNI_0023-250x150.jpg" alt="Rolf: As a token of my thanks, here. Take my Mama bear with you! On Toy Day!" class="wp-image-18135" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later rolled up two snowballs to make my first Snowmam of the winter. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250218_HNI_0024-250x150.jpg" alt="Snowmam: Oh my! I wonder who made this perfectly sculpted figure of mine!" class="wp-image-18136" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She was perfect, so she only needed three snowflakes for an item. I had two in my pockets already, so I quickly caught a third one. She gave me an ice floor for the trio of snowflakes, and I promptly sold it at Re-Tail for 8,888 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hornsby surprised me by telling me he&amp;#8217;s been looking for a sweet Mama bear. I&amp;#8217;m almost afraid to ask what that means! 😉 But he offered me 400 bells for it, and I agreed to the exchange.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250218_HNI_0025-250x150.jpg" alt="Hornsby: You might not know this, but I've been on the hunt for a sweet Mama bear." class="wp-image-18137" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t worry about buying her dinner. She&amp;#8217;s already stuffed.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I shot down a balloon present and found an IV drip inside! I guess my blood pressure was &lt;em&gt;sky high&lt;/em&gt;, but then it dropped like a rock. But I don&amp;#8217;t need the IV drip, so I just sold it&amp;#8230;for the cash flow. 😉 Sorry about the puns, but don&amp;#8217;t worry: I don&amp;#8217;t have any more &lt;em&gt;up my sleeve&lt;/em&gt;. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I saw a very large fish shadow in the river, and I fished out a stringfish! &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250219_HNI_0031-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeff, holding a stringfish: OH MY GOSH!" class="wp-image-18138" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The funny thing is, Mira actually asked me for a stringfish earlier in the day, but I told her no. I thought the odds of me catching one today were slim. You don&amp;#8217;t think Mira knew I&amp;#8217;d catch one, do you? Maybe she saw it in her magic mirror! &amp;#8220;&lt;em&gt;Mira, Mira, on the wall&amp;#8230;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8221; 😆 But it&amp;#8217;s okay, I&amp;#8217;d rather sell it anyway.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I listened in on a conversation between Jeremiah and Hornsby, and they were talking about food. (It seems that Inkwell was also listening in.) 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250219_HNI_0034-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: One thing that keeps me up at night is thinking about all the delicious foods I've never even heard of." class="wp-image-18139" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hornsby said that skyscraper windows are made of jelly, and Jeremiah knew it was true because he heard it on TV.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250219_HNI_0036-250x150.jpg" alt="Hornsby: I heard that skyscraper windows are actually made of jelly. That's why they bend without breaking." class="wp-image-18140" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;They also said that horchata runs through city pipes, and streetlights are made of lemon drops.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/20250219_HNI_0038-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: That show also said the streetlights are made of lemon drops!" class="wp-image-18141" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t know what TV show they were watching, but I&amp;#8217;m pretty sure they were sugar-coating the truth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I caught a few more snowflakes tonight, and I exchanged three of them for an ice dresser. But fortunately, winter is finally winding down! The snow will be gone by next Tuesday, and I&amp;#8217;ll be back at some point next week with another entry. Hope to see you then!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/02/19/sweet-mama-bear/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-02-19T20:54:39-05:00"&gt;February 19, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
